sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
This action fetches the build number for a job based on pre-defined build filter, such as latest successful or stable build, from the Jenkins server.

Inputs:

  • Job Path - The job path for which the build number is to be fetched. E.g. path1/job1.
  • Build Filter - Pre-defined Jenkins build filters which needs to be selected and the build number fetched is on the basis of it. Build Filter options:
    • Last Build - Will return build number of last build for the specified job.
    • Last Stable Build - Will return build number of last stable build for the specified job.
    • Last Successful Build - Will return build number of last successful build for the specified job.
    • Last Failed Build - Will return build number of last failed build for the specified job.
    • Last Unstable Build - Will return build number of last unstable build for the specified job.
    • Last Unsuccessful Build - Will return build number of last unsuccessful build for the specified job.
    • Last Completed Build - Will return build number of last completed build for the specified job.

Outputs:

  • Build Number - Build number of the requested job.
  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • You do not have enough permissions to perform this action in Jenkins server.
  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • Jenkins server is being restarted.
  • The requested job or the selected build status for the job doesn't exists or inaccessible, or the job has no build history.

To use this action, the corresponding Jenkins connection and credential must be created and associated with the Jenkins Connection & Credential alias.

Disclaimer:Jenkins and Jenkins logo are a registered trademark of Jenkins.

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
This action fetches the build number for a job based on pre-defined build filter, such as latest successful or stable build, from the Jenkins server.

Inputs:

  • Job Path - The job path for which the build number is to be fetched. E.g. path1/job1.
  • Build Filter - Pre-defined Jenkins build filters which needs to be selected and the build number fetched is on the basis of it. Build Filter options:
    • Last Build - Will return build number of last build for the specified job.
    • Last Stable Build - Will return build number of last stable build for the specified job.
    • Last Successful Build - Will return build number of last successful build for the specified job.
    • Last Failed Build - Will return build number of last failed build for the specified job.
    • Last Unstable Build - Will return build number of last unstable build for the specified job.
    • Last Unsuccessful Build - Will return build number of last unsuccessful build for the specified job.
    • Last Completed Build - Will return build number of last completed build for the specified job.

Outputs:

  • Build Number - Build number of the requested job.
  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • You do not have enough permissions to perform this action in Jenkins server.
  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • Jenkins server is being restarted.
  • The requested job or the selected build status for the job doesn't exists or inaccessible, or the job has no build history.

To use this action, the corresponding Jenkins connection and credential must be created and associated with the Jenkins Connection & Credential alias.
